Load-shedding images JOHANNESBURG -  Eskom will be implementing load reduction in Free State, and KwaZulu Natal on Saturday, to avoid network overloading in high-density areas. The power utility said load reduction will take place between 5 pm and 8 pm. READ: Eskom fraud case postponed to June Areas like Lejweleputswa, Ethekwini, Msinga and Newcastle will be affected by the load reduction. Provincial statements issued by Eskom name the specific areas that will be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
